.UPDATE...
Issued at 908 AM PDT Thu Jul 23 2026

The stratus pattern was more typical for this time of year and was
able to spread into the inland valleys overnight. However, dry air
aloft was able to disrupt the cloud deck across the Monterey Bay
region. We also had fog in places like Russian River Valley, Santa
Rosa, Half Moon Bay, Marina, and Monterey at times this morning.
However, conditions continue to improve across much of the region as
low clouds retreat back to the coast. No significant updates needed
to the ongoing forecast at this time. More on the Beach Hazards
Statement with the afternoon update.

RGass

